$ %SYSTEMROOT%\System32\lxss\tools

Among others, `%SYSTEMROOT%\System32\lxss\tools` seems to contain the → Linux/kernel[Linux kernel] (named `kernel`) for
→ Windows/Subsystem-for-Linux[WSL Version 2].
-
The default location of a kernel can be overwritten with the `kernel` directive in `→ Windows/dirs/Users/username/_wslconfig`.

Instructions on how this kernel can be installed or updated are found in → https://aka.ms/wsl2kernel.

{ Other files

  Other files besides the kernel that are found in this directory include:
    • bsdtar
    • ext4.vhdx.gz
    • init
    • initrd.img

}
